subjective: Patient reports a headache for the past two days, located in the back of the head. Patient drinks approximately four liters of water daily and sleeps around seven hours per night. Patient works at a computer for the entire day and uses normal vision correction glasses.
assessment: The headache could be related to eye strain from prolonged computer use.
plan: Recommend the patient discontinue using glasses and attempt to work without them to assess if this alleviates the headache.
